n Cooled Energy Core 249648 - Trimmer - Cold Damage Modifier 249107\n\nComments\n\nSupercharged Trimmers for players with Ai Expansion.\n"), array(39,"De'Valos Sleeves","\nIngredients\n\n High-Quality Cyber Armor Sleeves 21917\n<img src=rdb://13223>\n\n Powdered Viral-Bots 253149\n<img src=rdb://99236>\n\nRecipe\n\nHigh-Quality Cyber Armor Sleeves\n+\nPowdered Viral-Bots\n=\n<img src=rdb://255237>\n De'Valos Sleeves 253185\nSkills: | EE,NP |\n\nComments\n\nViral-Bots drop from alien Generals.\n"), array(40,"Enhanced Mantis Scissors","\nIngredients\n\n Mantis Scissors 157760\n<img src=rdb://158238>\n\n Diamond-Matrix Mesh 202266\n<img src=rdb://11615>\n\nRecipe\n\nDiamond-Matrix Mesh\n+\nMantis Scissors\n=\n<img src=rdb://158238>\n Enhanced Mantis Scissors 202265\nSkills: | ?? |\n\nComments\n\nNice weapon if you can get the parts.\n"), array(41,"Enhanced Queen Blade","\nIngredients\n\n Queen Blade 157761\n<img src=rdb://158239>\n\n Diamond-Matrix Mesh 202266\n<img src=rdb://11615>\n\nRecipe\n\nDiamond-Matrix Mesh\n+\nQueen Blade\n=\n<img src=rdb://158239>\n Enhanced Queen Blade 202264\nSkills: | ?? |\n\nComments\n\nNice weapon if you can get the parts.\n"), array(42,"Eye-Mutant Orb Laser","\nIngredients\n\n Eyemutant Eye 204974\n<img src=rdb://144708>\n\n Drum of Hydrochloric Acid 156051\n<img src=rdb://156211>\n\n Field Quantum Physics All-Purpose Tool 164558\n<img src=rdb://20410>\n\nRecipe\n\nDrum of Hydrochloric Acid\n+\nEyemutant Eye\n=\n<img src=rdb://152424>\n Inactive Eyemutant Orb Laser 204976\nSkills: | CH |\n\n\nField Quantum Physics All-Purpose Tool\n+\nInactive Eyemutant Orb Laser\n=\n<img src=rdb://152424>\n Eyemutant Orb Laser 204972\nSkills: | CH |\n\nComments\n\nAnother reason to kill those annoying eyemutants :)\n"), array(43,"Eyemutant Sinew Armor","\nIngredients\n\n Short 204767, Long 204769 or Eyemutant Sinews 204768\n<img src=rdb://156557>\n\n B.B.I. - Nano Enhanced B-12 Tanning Acid 162247\n<img src=rdb://156490>\n\n XXX-Plumbo Beer Can 130607\n<img src=rdb://37953>\n\n Small patch of soft bronto hide 162234, Patch of soft bronto hide 162230\nor Patch of hard bronto hide 162228\n<img src=rdb://161086>\n\nRecipe\n\n<highlight>Example: making of a sleeve<end>\n\nB.B.I. - Nano Enhanced B-12 Tanning Acid\n+\nPatch of soft bronto hide\n=\n<img src=rdb://161081>\n Patch of Soft Bronto Hide - Tanned 162242\nSkills: | CH,AG |\n\n\nXXX-Plumbo Beer Can\n+\nLong Eyemutant Sinews\n=\n<img src=rdb://156557>\n Long Eyemutant Sinews - Preserved 204772\nSkills: | ?? |\n\n\nLong Eyemutant Sinews - Preserved\n+\nPatch of Hard Bronto Hide - Tanned\n=\n<img src=rdb://37423>\n Eyemutant Sinew Sleeves - 1 Bundle 204791\nSkills: | CH |\n\nYou can apply 11 other Long Eyemutant Sinews - Preserved on the piece of armor you made to increase its QL.\n\nDetails\n\n Patch of Soft Bronto Hide 162230, Long Eyemutant Sinews 204769\n->\nEyemutant Sinew Sleeves\n( ie : Eyemutant Sinew Sleeves - 12 Bundles 204802 )\n\n Patch of Hard Bronto Hide 162228, Eyemutant Sinews 204768\n->\nEyemutant Sinew Boots\n( ie : Eyemutant Sinew Boots - 12 Bundles 204814 )\n\n Small Patch of Soft Bronto Hide 162234, Short Eyemutant Sinews 204767\n->\nEyemutant Sinew Gloves\n( ie : Eyemutant Sinew Gloves - 12 Bundles 204826 )\n\nComments\n\nEnforcer only. Interesting Cold and Fire damage bonuses !\n"), array(44,"Making Implants","\nA bit of Theory\n\nIn order to be efficient, The Basic Implant must be loaded with one or more Clusters. In fact, theses Basics Implants are only the support for the clusters which give the bonus. There's three kind of Clusters : Shining ones, Bright ones and finally Faded ones. Shining Clusters are the most powerful ones, Bright ones come second and Faded ones are the weakest, in theses proportions :\n\n Shining = Bright + Faded (to equal QL).\n Bright = 60% of Shining (to equal QL).\n Faded = 40% de Shining (to equal QL).\n\nEvery Basic Implant have three free slots. A free slot for every kind of Clusters. Each Cluster can be fitted in only one slot and on only one specific Basic implant.\n\nFor example:\n\nthe Cluster A Faded NanoCluster of Akimbo Style 101562 can only be fitted in the Faded slot of a Eye implant ( A Basic Eye Implant 101102).\n\nNow practical class\n\nTo combine a Cluster with an Implant (Basic or not, assuming that the targeted slot is free) you just got to find someone with enough Nano-Programming skill. If you proceed yourself to the combination, you have to pick up the cluster and Shift+Right click on the Implant.\n\nThings to know\n\nYou can combine a Cluster of an higher QL than the Implant, but the Cluster cannot be too low otherwise you won't be able to combine them. (tolerance : 14% for a Faded, 16% for a Bright and 18% for a Shining).\n\nCombining a Cluster with an Implant may result in a slightly higher Implant.\n\nThe QL of the Clusters combined with an Implant of a given QL are lowered or upped to this QL.\n\nYou can find there a very useful software to help you designing your Implants: Nanonanny /start http://www.timezulu.com.au/NanoNanny/.\n\nAll the Implants are requiring some skill in Treatement, as well as a Secondary Skill (a main attribute) dependingon the all clusters fitted in the Implant. According to this, it may be helpful to put a not so useful Cluster rather than another one, just to make this Secondary Skill deviate to a more higher main Attribute. Thus allowing you put higher QL of Implant.\n\nAnother way to solve this problem is using Implant Stepping. This tactic has been modified some patches ago, now you must have your Implant Slot in the Wear panel already empty before putting a new Implant. This still allow to have a intermediary implant in one Slot upping a main Attribute as you put your final Implant in another Slot (ie : you are two point short in Psy to put your QL60 Head implant, so you use a Chest Implant QL10, with a Bright Psychic Cluster on, which give you +5 Psy). This process still request you to plan your Implant Scheme a bit more...\n\nFixers can remove Clusters from the the Implant, resulting in a Basic Implant of the same QL. Still, during the process, all the Clusters incorporated in the Implant are lost. (Done with the help of a Implant Disassembly Clinic /tell {myname} recipe 51)\n"), array(45,"Building Nanoprograms","\nForward\n\nIn this recipe everything will be done by using:\n\n Instruction Disc (A Maker's Touch) 147348\n\nas an example.\n\nTo build a Nanoprogram, you first need to make a Programmed Photon Particle Emitter. The construction of this item require different ingredients depending of the Instruction Disc. In fact, to make it you need a Symbol Library. To know which one you need, just read the description of the Instruction Disc. In our case, it'll be a Symbol Library - Medical 144796. As for the Crystal Reflection Pattern (Medical one in this case).\n\nIngredients \n\n Instruction Disc (A Maker's Touch) 147348\n<img src=rdb://83413>\n\n Symbol Library - Medical 144796\n<img src=rdb://72779>\n\n Photon Particle Emitter 144788\n<img src=rdb://83869>\n\n Carbonrich Rock 150274\n<img src=rdb://72772>\n\n Jensen Personal Ore Extractor 150281\n<img src=rdb://149947>\n\n Isotope Separator 144785\n<img src=rdb://72783>\n\n Neutron Displacer 144784\n<img src=rdb://99235>\n\n Crystal Reflection Pattern - Medical 144778\n<img src=rdb://72776>\n\nRecipe \n\nInstruction Disc (A Maker's Touch)\n+\nSymbol Library - Medical\n=\n<img src=rdb://83118>\n Compiled Algorithm (A Maker's Touch) 145848\nSkills: | NP,CL |\n\n\nCompiled Algorithm (A Maker's Touch)\n+\nPhoton Particle Emitter\n=\n<img src=rdb://83706>\n Programmed Photon Particle Emitter (A Maker's Touch) 148848\nSkills: | NP |\n\n\nCarbonrich Rock\n+\nJensen Personal Ore Extractor\n=\n<img src=rdb://72766>\n Carbonrich Ore 144770\nSkills: | NP,CL |\n\n\nIsotope Separator\n+\nCarbonrich Ore\n=\n<img src=rdb://72765>\n Pure Carbon Crystal 144800\nSkills: | EE |\n\n\nPure Carbon Crystal\n+\nNeutron Displacer\n=\n<img src=rdb://72764>\n Program Crystal 144801\nSkills: | ME,QT |\n\n\nProgram Crystal\n+\nCrystal Reflection Pattern - Medical\n=\n<img src=rdb://72762>\n Prepared Program Crystal - Medical 144809\nSkills: | EE,QT |\n\n\nProgrammed Photon Particle Emitter (A Maker's Touch)\n+\nPrepared Program Crystal - Medical\n=\n<img src=rdb://42448>\n Nano Crystal (A Maker's Touch) 116804\nSkills: | ME,NP |\n\nComments\n\nOnce you have all the tools (and the reqs...), it's very profitable to build Nanoprograms. Especially since the cost of all the parts have been greatly reduced since 14.4 Patch. Moreover some Nanoprograms are only available by making them from the Instruction Disc...\n"), array(46,"Thick Flesh Hood","\nIngredients \n\n Monster Parts 42640\n<img src=rdb://144704>\n\n Programmed Photon Particle Emitter (Shape Soft Armor) 162222\n<img src=rdb://144476>\n\n Mass Relocating Robot 155591\n<img src=rdb://155928>\n\nRecipe \n\nProgrammed Photon Particle Emitter (Shape Soft Armor)\n+\nMass Relocating Robot\n=\n<img src=rdb://163857>\n Mass Relocating Robot (Shape Soft Armor) 162220\nSkills: | 2.5EE,2.5ME,2.5NP |\n\n\nMass Relocating Robot (Shape Soft Armor)\n+\nMonster Parts\n=\n<img src=rdb://23001>\n Thick Flesh Hood 163217\nSkills: | ME,INT |\n\nComments\n\nNo AC holes :)\n"), array(47,"Focus-Funneling Helper","\nIngredients \n\n Focus-Funneling Device 246206\n<img src=rdb://205507>\n\n Focus-Funneling Spirit 246207\n<img src=rdb://205507>\n\nAnd to upgrade it:\n\n Spirit Training Program 246209\n<img src=rdb://205512>\n\n Spirit Training Program 246211\n<img src=rdb://205512>\n\nRecipe \n\nFocus-Funneling Device\n+\nFocus-Funneling Spirit\n=\n<img src=rdb://205510>\n Primitive Focus-Funneling Helper 246208\nSkills: | ?? |\n\n\n<highlight>Then you can update it to fit in a different Hud (in order to wear 3 of them !!)<end>\n\nSpirit Training Program (Love)\n+\nPrimitive Focus-Funneling Helper\n=\n<img src=rdb://205511>\n Loving Focus-Funneling Helper 246210 ( for HUD 3 )\nSkills: | ?? |\n\nOR\n\nSpirit Training Program (Hate)\n+\nPrimitive Focus-Funneling Helper\n=\n<img src=rdb://205511>\n Rancorous Focus-Funneling Helper 246212 ( for HUD 1 )\nSkills: | ?? |\n\nComments\n\nAwesome item for twinking.\n"), array(48,"Guardian Conductor","\nIngredients \n\n Cloud of Polychromic Nanobots 202537\n<img src=rdb://203581>\n\n Guardian Conductor Building Kit 202572\n<img src=rdb://203579>\n\na Conductor Program\n( ie : Conductor of Presence Program 202566 )\n<img src=rdb://83790>\n\n HSR Compressed Regenerating Bioplate 202540\n<img src=rdb://203584>\n\nRecipe \n\nCloud of Polychromic Nanobots\n+\nGuardian Conductor Building Kit\n=\n<img src=rdb://203580>\n Guardian Conductor Controller 202574\nSkills: | 5.75EE,4CL,4NP |\n\n\nGuardian Conductor Controller\n+\nConductor of Presence Program\n=\n<img src=rdb://203580>\n Conductor of Presence Controller 202564\nSkills: | 5.75EE,4CL,4NP |\n\n\nConductor of Presence Controller\n+\nHSR Compressed Regenerating Bioplate\n=\n<img src=rdb://202151>\n Guardian Conductor of Presence 202987\nSkills: | 4ME |\n\nComments\n\nConstructed towers are so much better than prefab ones. Problem is that they dont seem to last long out there these days ;)\n"), array(49,"Half Digested Human Parts","\nIngredients \n\na Half Digested Human Parts\n( ie : Half Digested Human Torso 223567 )\n<img src=rdb://144701>\n\n Advanced Bio-Comminutor 154332\n<img src=rdb://149951>\n\nRecipe \n\nAdvanced Bio-Comminutor\n+\nHalf Digested Human Parts\n=\nan Implant\nSkills: | BE,CL |\n\nComments\n\nThere is a large chance to obtain a jobe implant. you can convert the Half Digested Human Parts by right clicking on it , but that way of processing is not sure.\n"), array(50,"Hologram","\nIngredients \n\n Expendable Hologram Camera 156054\n<img src=rdb://156092>\n\nA Hologram Projector Data\n( ie : Hologram PD: Barrel 160580 )\n<img src=rdb://20412>\n\nRecipe \n\nHologram Projector Data\n+\nExpendable Hologram Camera\n=\n<img src=rdb://156092>\nHologram Projector\n( ie : Hologram Projector: Barrel 160583 )\nSkills: | EE |\n\nComments\n\nAvailable only to agents, it allows them to hide disguise themselves as different objects, such as a crate >.<\n"), array(51,"Implant Disassembly Clinic","\nIngredients \n\n Portable Surgery Clinic 43551\n<img src=rdb://13369>\n\n Hacker Tool 87814\n<img src=rdb://99282>\n\n Implant Disassembly Unit 161864\n<img src=rdb://161874>\n\nRecipe \n\nHacker Tool\n+\nPortable Surgery Clinic\n=\n<img src=rdb://161872>\n Hacked Portable Surgery Clinic 161765\nSkills: | BE,CL |\n\n\nImplant Disassembly Unit\n+\nHacked Portable Surgery Clinic\n=\n<img src=rdb://161871>\n Implant Disassembly Clinic 161867\nSkills: | EE,CL |\n\nComments\n\nThis Clinic can only be worn by Fixers, but can be used by all. Added to the fact that it adds a bit of Treatement, you can use it to remove all the Clusters present on an Implant, thus creating a new Basic Implant of same QL. Don't forget that the Clusters are lost during the process.\n"), array(52,"Improved Immortal Katana","\nIngredients\n\n Faded Immortal Katana 154893\nor\n Broken Immortal Katana 154907\nor\n Immortal Katana 154505\n<img src=rdb://154506>\n\n SSC Reversive Energy-Packs 154943\n<img src=rdb://12667>\n\nRecipe\n\nSSC Reversive Energy-Packs\n+\nAn Immortal Katana\n=\n<img src=rdb://154506>\n Improved Immortal Katana 155863\nSkills: | EE |\n\nComments\n\nOnly the faded version of the Immortal Katana seems to be worth upgrading.\n"), array(53,"Improved Solar Trader Shotgun","\nIngredients\n\n Screwdriver 150922\n<img src=rdb://151011>\n\n Solar-Powered Shotgun 121570\n<img src=rdb://113988>\n\nRecipe\n\nScrewdriver\n+\nSolar-Powered Shotgun\n=\n<img src=rdb://113988>\n Improved Solar Trader Shotgun 243846\nSkills: | ?? |\n\nComments\n\nImprove your noob island weapon.\n"), array(54,"Improving Weapons","\nIngredients\n\nRobot Instruction Disc (Improve Weapons)\n( ie Robot Instruction Disc (Improve Slashing Weapons) 155533 )\n<img src=rdb:/