267703\nSkills: | NP1875 |\n\n\nAncient Scrap of Spirit Technical Knowledge\n+\nInert Knowledge Crystal\n=\n<img src=rdb://151030>\n Technical Knowledge Crystal 267740\nSkills: | CH1750 |\n\n\n<highlight>Next we combine the Knowledge Crystals:<end>\n\nCombat Knowledge Crystal\n+\nMedical Knowledge Crystal\n=\n<img src=rdb://156511>\n Incomplete Crystalised Memories 267781\nSkills: | QT1562 |\n\n\nIncomplete Crystalised Memories\n+\nTechnical Knowledge Crystal\n=\n<img src=rdb://156511>\n Complete Crystalised Memories 267778\nSkills: | QT1562 |\n\n\n<highlight>Now combine with your ready-made Bracer:<end>\n\nComplete Crystalised Memories\n+\nModified Ancient Combat Bracer\n=\n<img src=rdb://84062>\n Masterpiece Ancient Defensive Bracer 267798\nSkills: | ?? |\n\nComments\n\nAmazingly similar to Masterpiece Ancient Defensive Bracer /tell recipebot show me 595 recipe :P\n"), array(597,"Ancient Damage Generation Device","\nIngredients\n\n Ancient Medical Device 267736 Recipe /tell {myname} recipe 598\n<img src=rdb://218775>\n\n Ancient Damage Generation Device 267725\n<img src=rdb://218770>\n\nand <highlight>one<end> of the following items:\n\n Acid Gland Sample 267743\n<img src=rdb://144703>\n\n Fire Gland Sample 267741\n<img src=rdb://144705>\n\n Frost Gland Sample 267742\n<img src=rdb://144702>\n\n Radioactive Gland Sample 267744\n<img src=rdb://144705>\n\n Venom Gland Sample 267745\n<img src=rdb://253010>\n\nRecipe\n\nAncient Medical Device\n+\na gland sample (eg: Acid Gland Sample)\n=\n<img src=rdb://19860>\na sample of compound\n(eg: Sample of a chemical based compound 267732)\nSkills: | PT1750 |\n\n\nAncient Damage Generation Device\n+\nsample of compound (eg: Sample of a chemical based compound)\n=\n<img src=rdb://19860>\nAncient Generation Device\n(eg: Ancient Chemical Generation Device 267722)\nSkills: | CL1250 |\n\nDetails\n\nAcid Gland Sample = Ancient Chemical Generation Device 267722\nFire Gland Sample = Ancient Fire Generation Device 267720\nFrost Gland Sample = Ancient Cold Generation Device 267721\nRadioactive Gland Sample = Ancient Radiation Generation Device 267723\nVenom Gland Sample = Ancient Poison Generation Device 267724\n\nComments\n\nFinal product is used to change your damage type as well as give you 500 ACs of that type. :D\n"), array(598,"Ancient Medical Device","\nIngredients\n\n Energy Infused Crystal 267749\n<img src=rdb://156567>\n\n Inactive Ancient Medical Device 267735\n<img src=rdb://218774>\n\n Crystalised Memories of a Doctor 267726\n<img src=rdb://72771>\n\nRecipe\n\nEnergy Infused Crystal\n+\nInactive Ancient Medical Device\n=\n<img src=rdb://218774>\n Active Ancient Medical Device 267914\nSkills: | ME1500 |\n\n\nActive Ancient Medical Device\n+\nCrystalised Memories of a Doctor\n=\n<img src=rdb://218775>\n Ancient Medical Device 267736\nSkills: | ME1500 |\n\nComments\n\nAnother handy reusable tool for tradeskillers.\n"), array(600,"Frozen Yutto Remedies","\nIngredients \n\n *** With items gathered during the Penumbra quests and found in Alappaa, you can create 3 different kinds of Yutto Remedies. The base for all is the same, just the last components differ depending which type you wish to build. \nNote: Every step requires 1100 in Pharmacy skill and every product comes in stack of 5.\n *** \n\n Yuttos Filter 269884\n<img src=rdb://205505>\n\n Permafrost Residue 269872\n<img src=rdb://72768>\n\n Empty Permafrost Stimulant Chamber 269891\n<img src=rdb://100323>\n\n Volatile Permafrost Chemicals 269893\n<img src=rdb://100330>\nor\n Viscous Permafrost Chemicals 269894\n<img src=rdb://100337>\nor\n Regenerative Permafrost Chemicals 269895\n<img src=rdb://100333>\n\nRecipe \n\n<highlight>The Base:<end>\n\nYuttos Filter\n+\nPermafrost Residue\n=\n<img src=rdb://100323>\n Filtered Permafrost Residue 269890\nSkills: | PH |\n\nFiltered Permafrost Residue\n+\nEmpty Permafrost Stimulant Chamber\n=\n<img src=rdb://100315>\n Full Permafrost Stimulant Chamber 269892\nSkills: | PH |\n\n\n<highlight>The variations:<end>\n\nCold damage\nFull Permafrost Stimulant Chamber\n+\nVolatile Permafrost Chemicals\n=\n<img src=rdb://100314>\n Frozen Yuttos Remedy - Bane 269865\nSkills: | PH |\nNote: Runs Vengeful Ward of Penumbra in your NCU (+50 cold damage, +500 Cold AC)\n\nAdd all defence\nFull Permafrost Stimulant Chamber\n+\nViscous Permafrost Chemicals\n=\n<img src=rdb://100314>\n Frozen Yuttos Remedy - Icy Scales 269866\nSkills: | PH |\nNote: Runs Protective Ward of Penumbra in your NCU (+5 AAD, +500 Cold AC)\n\nHeal and Nano Delta\nFull Permafrost Stimulant Chamber\n+\nRegenerative Permafrost Chemicals\n=\n<img src=rdb://100314>\n Frozen Yuttos Remedy - Tonic 269867\nSkills: | PH |\nNote: Runs Regenerative Ward of Penumbra in your NCU (+2 heal delta, +2 nano delta, +500 Cold AC)\n"), array(601,"Anun Membrane Gloves","\nIngredients \n\n *** Only Bureaucrats and Traders can use these gloves. Since the\ntradeskill process creates a nondrop item, the user must do it him/herself.\nBasic ingredient for gloves are Anun Wings. They drop of any Anun mob, for\nhigher quality I would suggest hunting Anuns in PW or inside missions.\nYou'll also need Mass Relocating Robot (Shape Soft Armor) to complete the\nprocess.\n *** \n\n Anun Wing 248930\n<img src=rdb://144705>\n\n Mass Relocating Robot (Shape Soft Armor) 162220\n<img src=rdb://163857>\n\nRecipe \n\nAnun Wing\n+\nMass Relocating Robot (Shape Soft Armor)\n=\n<img src=rdb://159134>\n Anun Membrane Gloves 248928\nSkills: | requires 3.5 QL in Mech. Engi |"), array(602,"Ceremonial Chief's Headwear","\nIngredients \n\n *** There are actually two types of them, made either from Small\nObsidian Jar or Obsidian Jar. Jars drops of random mobs in Inner Sanctum.\nOnly thing needed to complete the process is Advanced Hacker Tool, available\nfrom Devices Terminal.\n *** \n\n Small Obsidian Jar 206477\n<img src=rdb://119173>\n\n Obsidian Jar 206457\n<img src=rdb://119185>\n\n Advanced Hacker Tool 87814\n<img src=rdb://99282>\n\nRecipe \n\n<highlight>Ceremonial Watchman's Hood<end>\n\nSmall Obsidian Jar\n+\nAdvanced Hacker Tool\n=\n<img src=rdb://205773>\n Ceremonial Watchman's Hood 206459\nSkills: | Requires 665 in Breaking & Entering Skill.|\n\n\n<highlight>Ceremonial Chief's Headwear<end>\n\nObsidian Jar\n+\nAdvanced Hacker Tool\n=\n<img src=rdb://205760>\n Ceremonial Chief's Headwear 206455\nSkills: | Requires 855 in Breaking & Entering Skill. |\n\n\nNote: Both headgears are leveling items (right-click on them to upgrade\nthem), Watchman's between QL 140 and 180, Chief's between QL 180 and 200.\nBoth are also title locked, Watchman's at title 4 to 5 and Chief's at title\n5"), array(603,"Cloak of the Reanimated","\nIngredients \n\n *** This cloak comes in 6 different types. Each are made in the\nsame way, apart from the Soul that determines the type of cloak you wish to\nmake.\nThe Reanimator's Cloak can be found in the Crypt of Home dungeon and the\nitems to upgrade it to a Cloak of the Reanimated drop off the Escaped\nPrisoners in Milky Way.\nYou will only need 1 Soul to make the base cloak. To further upgrade it you\nwill need 4 of each type.\n *** \n\n Reanimator's Cloak 245260\n<img src=rdb://22892>\n\n Soul of the Jester 274653\n<img src=rdb://274674>\n\n Soul of the Ranger 274654\n<img src=rdb://274675>\n\n Soul of the Summoner 274651\n<img src=rdb://274677>\n\n Soul of the Healer 274656\n<img src=rdb://274672>\n\n Soul of the Gladiator 274655\n<img src=rdb://274670>\n\n Soul of the Illusionist 274652\n<img src=rdb://274670>\n\n Empty Spirit Vest 274646\n<img src=rdb://274678>\n\n Soul Ripper 274650\n<img src=rdb://274684>\n\nRecipe \n\n<highlight>The Base Cloak of the Reanimated XXX:<end>\n\nReanimator's Cloak\n+\nSoul Ripper\n=\n<img src=rdb://227530>\n Explosion of Light 274728\nSkills: | ? |\nNote: Right clicking the Explosion of light will result in:\n\n Soul of the Reanimator 274649\n<img src=rdb://274676>\nand\n Grey Cloak 274647\n<img src=rdb://274671>\n\nNote: At this point you will set the type of your Cloak. Use the Soul of\nXXX (any of the 6 types) on your Soul of the Reanimator to make a Cloak of\nthat type.\n\nSoul of the Reanimator\n+\nSoul of the Jester\n=\n<img src=rdb://274674>\n Soul of the Reanimated Jester 274660\nSkills: | ? |\n\nEmpty Spirit Vest\n+\nSoul of the Reanimated Jester\n=\n<img src=rdb://274686>\n Jester's Spirit Vest 274668\n\nGrey Cloak\n+\nJester's Spirit Vest\n=\n<img src=rdb://274687>\n Cloak of the Reanimated Jester (1/5) 274718\n\n\n<highlight>Upgrading the Cloak of the Reanimated XXX:<end>\n\nSoul of the Ranger\n+\nSoul of the Gladiator\n=\n<img src=rdb://274673>\n Dull Combined Soul Crystal 274723\n\nDull Combined Soul Crystal\n+\nSoul of the Healer\n=\n<img src=rdb://274673>\n Dim Combined Soul Crystal 274724\n\nDim Combined Soul Crystal\n+\nSoul of the Summoner\n=\n<img src=rdb://274673>\n Sparkling Combined Soul Crystal 274725\n\nSparkling Combined Soul Crystal\n+\nSoul of the Illusionist\n=\n<img src=rdb://274673>\n Shining Combined Soul Crystal 274726\n\nShining Combined Soul Crystal\n+\nSoul of the Jester\n=\n<img src=rdb://274673>\n Awakened Soul Crystal 274727\n\nRepeat this step 4 times to end up with 4 Awakened Soul Crystals. Now\napply them to you cloak.\n\nAwakened Soul Crystal\n+\nCloak of the Reanimated Jester (1/5)\n=\n<img src=rdb://274687>\n Cloak of the Reanimated Jester (2/5) 274719\n\nAwakened Soul Crystal\n+\nCloak of the Reanimated Jester (2/5)\n=\n<img src=rdb://274687>\n Cloak of the Reanimated Jester (3/5) 274720\n\nAwakened Soul Crystal\n+\nCloak of the Reanimated Jester (3/5)\n=\n<img src=rdb://274687>\n Cloak of the Reanimated Jester (4/5) 274721\n\nAwakened Soul Crystal\n+\nCloak of the Reanimated Jester (4/5)\n=\n<img src=rdb://274687>\n Cloak of the Reanimated Jester (5/5) 274722"), array(604,"De-Hacked Frederickson Micro-kinetic Sleeves","\nIngredients \n\n *** Hack the sleeves with a hacker tool in order to make the clan\nversion of the omni sleeves. Neutrals can not wear them.\nNo trade skills required and the QL of the hacker tool does not matter.\n *** \n\n Frederickson Micro-kinetic Sleeves 152710\n<img src=rdb://81990>\n\n Advanced Hacker Tool 87814\n<img src=rdb://99282>\n\nRecipe \n\nFrederickson Micro-kinetic Sleeves\n+\nAdvanced Hacker Tool\n=\n<img src=rdb://81990>\n De-Hacked Frederickson Micro-kinetic Sleeves 286303\nSkills: No skills required."), array(605,"Hacked Light Omni-Tek Artillery Tank Armor","\nIngredients \n\n *** Since the standard issue can only be worn by Omni-Tek\npersonnel, several groups started to develop ways of enabling it to be worn\nby any faction.\nSoon, not one, but two methods were developed which removed the OT\nrestriction. Unfortunately both processes double the run speed handicap.\n *** \n\n Light Omni-Tek Artillery Tank Armor 204987\n<img src=rdb://41170>\n\n Advanced Hacker Tool 87814\n<img src=rdb://99282>\n\n Field Quantum Physics All-Purpose Tool 164558\n<img src=rdb://20410>\n\nRecipe \n\nLight Omni-Tek Artillery Tank Armor\n+\nAdvanced Hacker Tool\n=\n<img src=rdb://22393>\n Hacked Light Omni-Tek Artillery Tank Armor 204990\nSkills: Hacker tool needs to be at least 40% the ql of Tank Armor.\nYou'll need 5x Breaking and Entering skill to hack it.\n\nLight Omni-Tek Artillery Tank Armor\n+\nField Quantum Physics All-Purpose Tool\n=\n<img src=rdb://22393>\n Hacked Light Omni-Tek Artillery Tank Armor 204990\nFQP tool needs to be at least 40% the ql of Tank Armor. You'll need 5x Field\nQuantum Physics skill to hack it."), array(606,"Molybdenum Plate Armor Upgrades","\nIngredients \n\n Upgrade your Molybdenum Plate Armor (from Biodomes) with Black Molybdenum-Matrix of Xan and White Molybdenum-Matrix of Xan from Inside the\nMachine.\n\n Jathos' Molybdenum Plate Vest 252001\n<img src=rdb://252433>\n\n Kegern's Molybdenum Plate Helmet 252017\n<img src=rdb://252429>\n\n Jathos' Molybdenum Plate Boots 252002\n<img src=rdb://252431>\n\n Kegern's Molybdenum Plate Gloves 252018\n<img src=rdb://252440>\n\n Black Molybdenum-Matrix of Xan 272458\n<img src=rdb://272534>\n\n White Molybdenum-Matrix of Xan 272459\n<img src=rdb://272535>\n\nRecipe \n\nJathos' Molybdenum Plate Vest\n+\nBlack Molybdenum-Matrix of Xan\n=\n<img src=rdb://272440>\n Enhanced Jathos' Molybdenum Plate Vest 272444\nSkills: | ? |\n\nKegern's Molybdenum Plate Helmet\n+\nBlack Molybdenum-Matrix of Xan\n=\n<img src=rdb://272431>\n Enhanced Kegern's Molybdenum Plate Helmet 272454\nSkills: | ? |\nNote: Black Molybdenum-Matrix of Xan is used to upgrade both types of armor, Kegern's as well as Jathos, but only vest and helmet pieces. And if you have already upgraded helmet with Action Probability Estimator from Apf, you won't be able to do this combine.\n\n\nJathos' Molybdenum Plate Boots\n+\nWhite Molybdenum-Matrix of Xan\n=\n<img src=rdb://272442>\n Enhanced Jathos' Molybdenum Plate Boots 272445\nSkills: | ? |\n\nKegern's Molybdenum Plate Gloves\n+\nWhite Molybdenum-Matrix of Xan\n=\n<img src=rdb://272433>\n Enhanced Kegern's Molybdenum Plate Gloves 272453\nSkills: | ? |\nNote: White Molybdenum-Matrix of Xan is used to upgrade both types of armor, Kegern's as well as Jathos, but only boots, gloves, sleeves and pant pieces."), array(607,"Photon Embedded Cloak","\nIngredients \n\n *** Your shining light in the darkness!\n *** \n\n Light Bar 252157\n<img src=rdb://37996>\nor\n A Never-ending Being of Light 262604\n<img src=rdb://262646>\n\n White Trenchcoat 81969\n<img src=rdb://82001>\n\nRecipe \n\nLight Bar\n+\nWhite Trenchcoat\n=\n<img src=rdb://281785>\n Photon Embedded Cloak 281777\nSkills: | None | \nor\nA Never-ending Being of Light\n+\nWhite Trenchcoat\n=\n<img src=rdb://281785>\n Photon Embedded Cloak 281777\nSkills: | None | "), array(608,"Cranium Nano Cloak","\nIngredients \n\n *** The Red Cranium Nano Cloak is a Clan & Meta-Physicist only\nitem but you can remove some of these requirements. Doing so however will\nalso remove or lower some of the modifiers: Nano Init. and MaxNanoEnergy.\nThe quality of the Field Quantum Physics All-Purpose Tool and Hacker Tool\nmust be at least 40% of QL of the cloak.\n *** \n\n Red Cranium Nano Cloak 204996\n<img src=rdb://85941>\n\n Field Quantum Physics All-Purpose Tool 164558\n<img src=rdb://20410>\n\n Advanced Hacker Tool 87814\n<img src=rdb://99282>\n\nRecipe \n\nRed Cranium Nano Cloak\n+\nField Quantum Physics All-Purpose Tool\n=\n<img src=rdb://85942>\n Grey Cranium Nano Cloak 204998\nSkills: |FQP tool needs to be at least 40% the ql of Tank Armor. You'll\nneed 5x Field Quantum Physics skill to hack it.|\n\nGrey Cranium Nano Cloak\n+\nAdvanced Hacker Tool\n=\n<img src=rdb://85945>\n Grey Nano Cloak 205000\nSkills: |Hacker Tool needs to be at least 40% of the ql of the Cloak.\nRequires 6X of cloaks QL of Breaking & Entering and the QL of the.|"), array(609,"Enhanced Pads of Dedication","\nIngredients \n\n *** Omni-Tek employees and Neutrals will be happy to know that their Pads of Dedication which can be obtained by doing the Shoulderpads Quest can be upgraded even further. What's even better is that the upgrade doesn't require any skills to do.\n\nAll you will need besides your Pads is an Omnifier. You can find it in missions, it's a common from mobs and you can also find it in chests.\n *** \n\n Omnifier 208312\n<img src=rdb://156479>\n\n Pads of Dedication 157998\n<img src=rdb://31537>\n\nRecipe \n\nOmnifier\n+\nPads of Dedication\n=\n<img src=rdb://31537>\n Enhanced Pads of Dedication 209237\nSkills: | None | \n\nComparing stats between the original and upgraded versions, most of them have been enhanced by 50%. Oh and the Pads turn into a nice shiny black color which perfectly matches the popular Omni-Tek Armed Forces armor omnis wear."), array(610,"Alappaa shoulderpads","\nIngredients \n\n *** You'll get parts for upgrade in Alappaa and in Dustbrigade Outpost. There are 3 different types you can upgrade them into. But first you need to unfreeze them.\n *** \n\n Frozen Shoulderpads 269896\n<img src=rdb://269968>\n\n Permafrost Melting Tool 269805\n<img src=rdb://269844>\n\n Permafrost Armor Component 269937\n<img src=rdb://269936>\n\n Combat Program 269946\n<img src=rdb://269949>\nor\n Nano Technology Program 269945\n<img src=rdb://269950>\nor\n Melee Program 269947\n<img src=rdb://269948>\n\n-And the upgrades-\n\n Master Combat Program 269960\n<img src=rdb://269949>\nor\n Master Nano Technology Program 269959\n<img src=rdb://269950>\nor\n Master Melee Program 269961\n<img src=rdb://269948>\n\nRecipe \n\n Unfreezing the shoulderpads \n\nFrozen Shoulderpads\n+\nPermafrost Melting Tool\n=\n<img src=rdb://269968>\n Shoulderpads of the Icy Wastes 269897\nSkills: | None | \n\n Superior Icy Shoulderpads of Explosive Power \n\nCombat Program\n+\nPermafrost Armor Component\n=\n<img src=rdb://269936>\n Combat Attuned Permafrost Armor Component 269938\nSkills: | 1500 ME | \n\nShoulderpads of the Icy Wastes\n+\nCombat Attuned Permafrost Armor Component\n=\n<img src=rdb://269963>\n Icy Shoulderpads of Explosive Power 269898\nSkills: | none | \n\nIcy Shoulderpads of Explosive Power\n+\nMaster Combat Program\n=\n<img src=rdb://269963>\n Superior Icy Shoulderpads of Explosive Power 269899\nSkills: | none | \n\n Superior Icy Shoulderpads of the Powerful Mind \n\nNano Technology Program\n+\nPermafrost Armor Component\n=\n<img src=rdb://269936>\n Nano Attuned Permafrost Armor Component 269939\nSkills: | 1500 ME | \n\nShoulderpads of the Icy Wastes\n+\nNano Attuned Permafrost Armor Component\n=\n<img src=rdb://269962>\n Icy Shoulderpads of Explosive Power 269898\nSkills: | none | \n\nIcy Shoulderpads of the Powerful Mind\n+\nMaster Nano Technology Program\n=\n<img src=rdb://269962>\n Superior Icy Shoulderpads of the Powerful Mind 269900\nSkills: | none | \n\n Superior Icy Shoulderpads of Brawn \n\nMelee Program\n+\nPermafrost Armor Component\n=\n<img src=rdb://269936>\n Melee Attuned Permafrost Armor Component 269940\nSkills: | 1500 ME | \n\nShoulderpads of the Icy Wastes\n+\nMelee Attuned Permafrost Armor Component\n=\n<img src=rdb://269964>\n Icy Shoulderpads of Brawn 269902\nSkills: | none | \n\nIcy Shoulderpads of Brawn\n+\nMaster Melee Program\n=\n<img src=rdb://269964>\n Superior Icy Shoulderpads of Brawn 269903\nSkills: | none | "), array(611,"De'Valos Protection Ring","\nIngredients \n\n *** Drops from the Bosses in Sector 35. *** \n\n De'Valos Radiation Protection Ring 257117\n<img src=rdb://281266>\n\n De'Valos Lava Protection Ring 257116\n<img src=rdb://281266>\n\n Hold Hell at Bay 231234\n<img src=rdb://234505>\n\nRecipe \n\n This tradeskill process does not require any skill whatsoever, just combine rings. \n\nDe'Valos Radiation Protection Ring\n+\nDe'Valos Lava Protection Ring\n=\n<img src=rdb://281266>\n De'Valos Radiation and Lava Protection Ring 281264\nSkills: | None | \n\nDe'Valos Radiation and Lava Protection Ring\n+\nHold Hell at Bay\n=\n<img src=rdb://281266>\n De'Valos Protection Ring 281267\nSkills: | None | "), array(612,"Nano Breed Service Suit Armor","\nIngredients \n\n *** Before you go on, this armor is one of rarest found on Rubi-Ka. So far only handfull of pieces were found, even if it made ingame years ago (only confirmed drop is reported from lvl 59 Nano Breed mob inside mission). And since it's limited buffs, mostly collectors would be interested in it. *** \n\n Nano Breed Survival Suit Body Armor 206609\n<img src=rdb://13252>\n\n Nano Breed Survival Suit Boots 206610\n<img src=rdb://155112>\n\n Nano Breed Survival Suit Pants 206611\n<img src=rdb://13302>\n\n Nano Breed Survival Suit Sleeves 206608\n<img src=rdb://22949>\n\n Inactive OT Metamorphing Liquid Nanobots 164952\n<img src=rdb://156496>\n\n Nano Programming Interface 161699\n<img src=rdb://99279>\n\n Advanced Hacker Tool 87814\n<img src=rdb://99282>\n\nRecipe \n\n The Nano Programming Interface can be bought from tools terminals. Inactive OT Metamorphing Liquid Nanobots are in armor and clothing components terminals. Hacker Tool drop from missions and can also be purchased at regular shops. \n\nFirst, you need to prepare OT Metamorphing Liquid Nanobots. If you want fully augmented armor, you'll need 10 pieces of them for each armor piece you're making. Nano Programming Interface doesn't get used up in the process.\n\nInactive OT Metamorphing Liquid Nanobots\n+\nNano Programming Interface\n=\n<img src=rdb://156492>\n Activated OT Metamorphing Liquid Nanobots 164954\nSkills: | x2.5 CL x4 NP based on QL of Nanobots | \nNotes: Inactive OT Nanobots must be within 90% of armor. \n\n Once this is sorted, you're ready to start on armor itself.\n\nNano Breed Survival Suit Body Armor\n+\nAdvanced Hacker Tool\n=\n<img src=rdb://13252>\n Hacked Nano Breed Survival Suit Body Armor 206614\nSkills: | 48 BE | \n\nHacked Nano Breed Survival Suit Body Armor\n+\nActivated OT Metamorphing Liquid Nanobots\n=\n<img src=rdb://13252>\n Nano Breed Service Suit Body Armor - Once Augmented 206645\nSkills: | 60 NP | \n\n You can repeat this process 9 more times each time after the 2nd upgrade the NP increases by 60 points to a final skill of 540 NP on final upgrade.\n\nNano Breed Service Suit Body Armor - Nine Times Augmented\n+\nActivated OT Metamorphing Liquid Nanobots\n=\n<img src=rdb://13252>\n Nano Breed Service Suit Body Armor - Maximum Augmented 206636\nSkills: | 540 NP | \n\n If you manage to collect all 5 pieces of armor (4 different pieces and extra sleeve, since there aren't that many one-armed characters around) and upgrade them to maximum, you'll get bonus of:\n\nMaxNanoEnergy: 1100\nNanoC.Init: 250\n\nWith that, only practical use for it, that I can think of, is maybe some NT or Doctor twink, but they would still be penalized for lack of AC or Nano Skill mods on this armor."), array(613,"Sabotaging Surgeons Cloak","\nIngredients \n\n *** In order to sabotage anything, you need to get your hands on it first. In case of Omni-Med Field Surgeons Cloak, it drops off Dyna and mission bosses. It drops in various ql, highest found so far being ql 200. Whole sabotaging business is actually really easy, all you need is Advanced Hacker Tool. *** \n\n Omni-Med Field Surgeons Cloak 201235\n<img src=rdb://120623>\n\n Advanced Hacker Tool 87814\n<img src=rdb://99282>\n\nRecipe \n\nOmni-Med Field Surgeons Cloak\n+\nAdvanced Hacker Tool\n=\n<img src=rdb://120623>\n Sabotaged Omni-Med Field Surgeons Cloak 201238\nSkills: | 4.75 BE 3.25x CL based on QL | \n\n If person doing tradeskills have high enough skills, end product can be higher ql as 200. Hacking the cloak also results in loosing Omni tag and BiologicalMetamorphosis buff. "), array(614,"Sureshot Glasses","\nIngredients \n\n *** Sureshot Glasses drop from Alien generals. But in case you're tired of farming them, there's a way to build them. *** \n\n Wire Drawing Machine 150917\n<img src=rdb://149952>\n\n Personal Furnace 150930\n<img src=rdb://290713>\n\n Small Platinum Ingot 151363\n<img src=rdb://289751>\n\n Crystalline Disk 253139\n<img src=rdb://100319>\n\nRecipe \n\n Now it's time to put everything together: \n\nSmall Platinum Ingot\n+\nPersonal Furnace\n=\n<img src=rdb://290708>\n Liquid Platinum 151361\nSkills: | 3.8x ME based on QL | \n\nLiquid Platinum\n+\nWire Drawing Machine\n=\n<img src=rdb://151017>\n Platinum Filigree Wire 151360\nSkills: | 5.5x ME, 1.8x Agility | \n\nCrystalline Disk\n+\nPlatinum Filigree Wire\n=\n<img src=rdb://86483>\n Sureshot Glasses 253183\nSkills: | 5x EE,ME | \n\n At start of guide we said you'll need at least ql 100 Crystalline Disk. Why? Simply because Sureshot Glasses come in quality range of 100-300. Another thing to watch while making them is title requirement to wear (ql 100-119 for tlt1, 120-159 for tlt2, 160-199 for tlt3, 200-239 for tlt4, 240-279 for tlt5, 280+ for tlt6). "), array(615,"Aggression Trimmer","\nIngredients \n\n Every Engineer wants to make his/her bot as powerful as possible, the reason why trimming bots is one of the most common tactics to enhance bots abilities. Trimming however does come at a price, by boosting one part of the bot's functions another is lowered. For example, if you use a Trimmer to raise the defense of your bot then the aggressiveness of it will be lowered. Trimmers can be purchased from general shops, but this specific Trimmer can only be built, and it has one advantage...it will increase the chances of your bot keeping aggro on whatever it's fighting, at no cost of other skills. This means an Engineer will be less likely of getting attacked leaving his/her bot to do all the fighting. The lowest version Aggression Trimmer you'll be able to assemble is QL 30, keep that in mind when buying parts. \n\n Chemical Impact Injector 142911\n<img src=rdb://130815>\n\n XU-11 Serum 154909\n<img src=rdb://100338>\n\n Trimmer Casing 154938\n<img src=rdb://154935>\n\n All of them can be found at general shops. It could cost you a few hundred thousand credits, so be sure to have funds to make the purchases. \n\nRecipe \n\n Now it's time to put everything together: \n\nXU-11 Serum\n+\nChemical Impact Injector\n=\n<img src=rdb://130814>\n Modified Chemical Impact Injector 154911\nSkills: | 1.8x CHEM based on QL | \nNote: The XU-11 Serum needs to be within 60% of the QL of the Chemical Impact Injector for this combine to work. Note that the Modified Chemical Impact Injector will raise a few QLs during this process (use the Tradeskill Kit to check). \n\nModified Chemical Impact Injector\n+\nTrimmer Casing\n=\n<img src=rdb://292747>\n Trimmer - Increase Aggressiveness 154940\nSkills: | 3.7x ME* | \n\n The Modified Chemical Impact Injector needs to be within 90% of the QL of the Trimmer Casing for this combine to work. Use the Tradeskill Kit to adjust the final QL of the trimmer.\n\nThe Trimmer - Increase Aggressiveness requires Mechanical Engineering and Computer Literacy to use. Also the Trimmer only works on robotic pets... not on Metaphysicist pets.\nA quality level 200 Trimmer requires 751 Mechanical Engineering and 551 Computer Literacy\n\nNote: Remember that as you upgrade your bot to a strong version, you should do the same with the Trimmer.\n\n* May also require a small amount of Computer Literacy (less than x1.6). "), array(616,"AI Yalms","\nIngredients \n\n Looking for a snazzy new yalm? Our friend Uncle Bazzit is selling a few new yalm upgrades, for a price of course.\nHead to Meetmedere, to Uncle Bazzit's shop. The upgrades are found in the shop terminal, in the back left of the room.\n\n Yalmaha 29600 - Obsidian Upgrade Kit 254817\n<img src=rdb://20406>\n\n Yalmaha 29600 - Pearl Upgrade Kit 254818\n<img src=rdb://20406>\n\n Yalmaha 29610 - Sunrise Upgrade Kit 254819\n<img src=rdb://81786>\n\n Yalmaha 29610 - Daylight Upgrade Kit 254820\n<img src=rdb://81786>\n\n Yalmaha 29610 - Sunset Upgrade Kit 254821\n<img src=rdb://81786>\n\n Yalmaha 29610 - Dusk Upgrade Kit 254823\n<img src=rdb://81786>\n\n Yalmaha XL - 29478 96088\n<img src=rdb://38023>\n\nRecipe \n\nNote:End QL of the yalm is determined by Comp Lit. To make a ql300 (results in lowest vehicle air), you will need 1500 CL.\nYou will need at least 750 Computer Literature to make lowest ql available. Ql of Yalmaha XL - 29478 you use, doesn not matter\n\nYalmaha 29600 - Obsidian Upgrade Kit\n+\nYalmaha XL - 29478\n=\n<img src=rdb://255895>\n Yalmaha - 29600 - Obsidian 253582\nSkills: | CL |\n\nYalmaha 29600 - Pearl Upgrade Kit\n+\nYalmaha XL - 29478\n=\n<img src=rdb://255900>\n Yalmaha - 29600 - Pearl 253584\nSkills: | CL |\n\nYalmaha 29610 - Sunrise Upgrade Kit\n+\nYalmaha XL - 29478\n=\n<img src=rdb://255896>\n Yalmaha - 29610 - Sunrise 253574\nSkills: | CL |\n\nYalmaha 29610 - Daylight Upgrade Kit\n+\nYalmaha XL - 29478\n=\n<img src=rdb://255898>\n Yalmaha - 29610 - Daylight 253576\nSkills: | CL |\n\nYalmaha 29610 - Sunset Upgrade Kit\n+\nYalmaha XL - 29478\n=\n<img src=rdb://255897>\n Yalmaha - 29610 - Sunset 253578\nSkills: | CL |\n\nYalmaha 29610 - Dusk Upgrade Kit\n+\nYalmaha XL - 29478\n=\n<img src=rdb://255899>\n Yalmaha - 29600 - Dusk 253580\nSkills: | CL |"), array(620,"Mass Relocating Robot","\nIngredients \n\n There are 5 different Mass Relocating Robots. Each one requires a different Instruction Disc or Programmed Photon Particle Emitter.\nThe weapon PPPE's drop from level 10-30 mobs, the Shape Hard/Soft Armor PPPE's are harder to find as they drop from QL 60 dyna and mission bosses.\n\n Robot Instruction Disc (Improve Crushing Weapons) 155906\n<img src=rdb://83347>\n\n Robot Instruction Disc (Improve Thrusting Weapons) 155907\n<img src=rdb://83443>\n\n Robot Instruction Disc (Improve Slashing Weapons) 155533\n<img src=rdb://83446>\n\n Programmed Photon Particle Emitter (Shape Hard Armor) 162221\n<img src=rdb://144466>\n\n Programmed Photon Particle Emitter (Shape Soft Armor) 162222\n<img src=rdb://144476>\n\n Symbol Library - Space 144790\n<img src=rdb://72782>\n\n Photon Particle Emitter 144812\n<img src=rdb://83869>\n\n Ultimate Mass Relocating Robot 155592\n<img src=rdb://155928>\n\nRecipe \n\nNote: When making a Weapon MRR, you will need to upgrade the Robot Instruction Disks to Programmed Photon Particle Emitters like this:\n\nRobot Instruction Disc (Improve Crushing Weapons)\n+\nSymbol Library - Space\n=\n<img src=rdb://83052>\n Robot Compiled Algorithm (Improve Crushing Weapons) 155903\nSkills: | 4 x QL of the Instruction Disk in NP and CL |\nNote: QL of the Symbol Library must be at least 25% of the Robot Instruction Disk\n\nRobot Compiled Algorithm (Improve Crushing Weapons)\n+\nPhoton Particle Emitter\n=\n<img src=rdb://83640>\n Programmed Photon Particle Emitter (Improve Crushing Weapons) 155905\nSkills: | 4.25 x QL of the Instruction Disk in NP |\nNote: QL of the Photon Particle Emitter must be at least 50% of the Robot Instruction Disk\n\n\nNow combine your PPPE (XXX) with an Ultimate Mass Relocating Robot:\n\nProgrammed Photon Particle Emitter (Improve Crushing Weapons)\n+\nUltimate Mass Relocating Robot\n=\n<img src=rdb://155927>\n Mass Relocating Robot (Improve Crushing Weapons) 155924\n"), array(621,"Ancient Defender","\nIngredients \n\n Both parts required for this process can be found in Albtraum\n\n Empty Ancient Device 267709\n<img src=rdb://218753>\n\n Crystalised Memories of a Defender 267711\n<img src=rdb://72771>\n\nRecipe \n\nEmpty Ancient Device\n+\nCrystalised Memories of a Defender\n=\n<img src=rdb://218752>\n Ancient Defender 267627\nSkills: | 1250 CL |\n\nNote: You can upgrade this item with a Dust Brigade Notum Infuser 274552\nThe recipe can be found here: Infused Ancient Defender /tell {myname} recipe 628"), array(622,"Ancient Medical Bracer","\nIngredients \n\n All parts required for this process can be found in Albtraum. \nYou will need to build an Ancient Engineering Device as well if you do not have one already. \nA link to this tradeskill process is included\n\n Crystalised Memories of a Doctor 267726\n<img src=rdb://72771>\n\n Crystalised Memories of a Surgeon 267728\n<img src=rdb://72771>\n\n Ancient Scrap of Spirit Knowledge 267677\n<img src=rdb://163575>\n\n Ancient Scrap of Saturated Spirit Knowledge 267679\n<img src=rdb://163575>\n\n Inactive Ancient Bracer 267746\n<img src=rdb://290853>\n\n Inert Knowledge Crystal 267737\n<img src=rdb://151030>\n\n Ancient Engineering Device 267751\n<img src=rdb://156095>\nNote:To build your Ancient Engineering Device, go here:\n Ancient Engineering Device /tell {myname} recipe 594\n\nRecipe \n\nCrystalised Memories of a Doctor\n+\nCrystalised Memories of a Surgeon\n=\n<img src=rdb://72769>\n Combined Crystalised Medical Memories 267729\nSkills: | 1750 CH |\n\nAncient Scrap of Spirit Knowledge\n+\nAncient Scrap of Saturated Spirit Knowledge\n=\n<img src=rdb://163575>\n Ancient Scrap of Condensed Spirit Knowledge 267680\nSkills: | 1750 PT |\n\nAncient Scrap of Condensed Spirit Knowledge\n+\nCombined Crystalised Medical Memories\n=\n<img src=rdb://163575>\n Ancient Scrap of Spirit Medical Knowledge 267727\nSkills: | 1750 CH |\n\nAncient Scrap of Spirit Medical Knowledge\n+\nInert Knowledge Crystal\n=\n<img src=rdb://151030>\n Medical Knowledge Crystal 267738\nSkills: | 1750 CH |\n\nAncient Engineering Device\n+\nInactive Ancient Bracer\n=\n<img src=rdb://290847>\n Active Ancient Bracer 267747\nSkills: | 1500 ME |\n\nActive Ancient Bracer\n+\nMedical Knowledge Crystal\n=\n<img src=rdb://290851>\n Ancient Medical Bracer 267752\nSkills: | 1250 ME |"), array(623,"Ancient Nano Enhancer","\nIngredients \n\n Both parts required for this process can be found in Albtraum\n\n Empty Ancient Device 267709\n<img src=rdb://218753>\n\n Crystalised Memories of a Scientist 267713\n<img src=rdb://72771>\n\nRecipe \n\nEmpty Ancient Device\n+\nCrystalised Memories of a Scientist\n=\n<img src=rdb://218768>\n Ancient Nano Enhancer 267712\nSkills: | 1250 CL |\n\nNote: You can upgrade this item with a Dust Brigade Notum Infuser 274552\nThe recipe for this can be found here: Infused Ancient Nano Enhancer /tell {myname} recipe 630"), array(624,"Ancient Technical Bracer","\nIngredients \n\n All parts required for this process can be found in Albtraum. \nYou will need to build an Ancient Engineering Device as well if you do not have one already. \nA link to this tradeskill process is included\n\n Crystalised Memories of a Technician 267698\n<img src=rdb://72770>\n\n Crystalised Memories of a Mechanic 267701\n<img src=rdb://72771>\n\n Ancient Scrap of Spirit Knowledge 267677\n<img src=rdb://163575>\n\n Ancient Scrap of Saturated Spirit Knowledge 267679\n<img src=rdb://163575>\n\n Inactive Ancient Bracer 267746\n<img src=rdb://290853>\n\n Inert Knowledge Crystal 267737\n<img src=rdb://151030>\n\n Ancient Engineering Device 267751\n<img src=rdb://156095>\nNote:To build your Ancient Engineering Device, go here:\n Ancient Engineering Device /tell {myname} recipe 594\n\nRecipe \n\nCrystalised Memories of a Technician\n+\nCrystalised Memories of a Mechanic\n=\n<img src=rdb://72769>\n Combined Crystalised Technical Memories 267702\nSkills: | 1875 NP |\n\nAncient Scrap of Spirit Knowledge\n+\nAncient Scrap of Saturated Spirit Knowledge\n=\n<img src=rdb://163575>\n Ancient Scrap of Condensed Spirit Knowledge 267680\nSkills: | 1750 PT |\n\nCombined Crystalised Technical Memories\n+\nAncient Scrap of Condensed Spirit Knowledge\n=\n<img src=rdb://163575>\n Ancient Scrap of Spirit Technical Knowledge 267703\nSkills: | 1875 NP |\n\nAncient Scrap of Spirit Technical Knowledge\n+\nInert Knowledge Crystal\n=\n<img src=rdb://151030>\n Technical Knowledge Crystal 267740\nSkills: | 1750 CH |\n\nAncient Engineering Device\n+\nInactive Ancient Bracer\n=\n<img src=rdb://290847>\n Active Ancient Bracer 267747\nSkills: | 1500 ME |\n\nActive Ancient Bracer\n+\nTechnical Knowledge Crystal\n=\n<img src=rdb://290852>\n Ancient Technical Bracer 267754\nSkills: | 1250 ME |"), array(625,"Ancient Skills Library","\nIngredients \n\n Both parts required for this process can be found in Albtraum\n\n Empty Ancient Device 267709\n<img src=rdb://218753>\n\n Crystalised Memories of a Engineer 267714\n<img src=rdb://72771>\n\nRecipe \n\nEmpty Ancient Device\n+\nCrystalised Memories of a Engineer\n=\n<img src=rdb://218759>\n Ancient Skills Library 267652\nSkills: | 1250 CL |"), array(626,"Perfected Infused Dust Brigade Bracer","\nIngredients \n\n Dust Brigade Notum Infusers are used in 15 processes, most of them for upgrading Basic Infused Dust Brigade Bracers. \nOther 5 tradeskills include Dust Brigade Engineer Pistol upgrade as well as improving 4 gizmos associated with Albtraum.\n\n Basic Infused Dust Brigade Bracer 274541\n<img src=rdb://290459>\n\n Dust Brigade Notum Infuser 274552\n<img src=rdb://218768>\n\nRecipe \n\nDust Brigade Notum Infuser\n+\nBasic Infused Dust Brigade Bracer\n=\n<img src=rdb://290461>\n Improved Infused Dust Brigade Bracer - Tier 1 274542\nSkills: | CL 2000 |\n\nDust Brigade Notum Infuser\n+\nImproved Infused Dust Brigade Bracer - Tier 1\n=\n<img src=rdb://290462>\n Improved Infused Dust Brigade Bracer - Tier 2 274543\nSkills: | CL 2000 |\n\nDust Bri