\n<img src=rdb://45782>\nor\n Superior Perennium Beamer 246421\n<img src=rdb://45783>\n\n Perennium Blaster Rebuild Kit 260724\n<img src=rdb://205502>\nor\n Perennium Sniper Rebuild Kit 260726\n<img src=rdb://205502>\nor\n Perennium Beamer Rebuild Kit 260725\n<img src=rdb://205502>\n\n Lord of Anger 244802\n<img src=rdb://210184>\nor\n Lord of Angst 244821\n<img src=rdb://245082>\nor\n Lord of Envy 244836\n<img src=rdb://245082>\n\nRecipe \n\n<highlight>Superior Rebuilt Perennium Sniper<end>\n\nLord of Angst\n+\nPerennium Sniper Rebuild Kit\n=\n<img src=rdb://205501>\n Perennium Sniper Rebuild Kit 260727\n\nPerennium Sniper Rebuild Kit\n+\nSuperior Perennium Sniper\n=\n<img src=rdb://245082>\n Superior Rebuilt Perennium Sniper 260720\n\n<highlight>Superior Rebuilt Perennium Beamer<end>\n\nLord of Envy\n+\nPerennium Beamer Rebuild Kit\n=\n<img src=rdb://205501>\n Perennium Beamer Rebuild Kit 260728\n\nPerennium Sniper Rebuild Kit\n+\nSuperior Perennium Beamer\n=\n<img src=rdb://244836>\n Superior Rebuilt Perennium Beamer 260713\n\n<highlight>Superior Rebuilt Perennium Blaster<end>\n\nLord of Envy\n+\nPerennium Blaster Rebuild Kit\n=\n<img src=rdb://205501>\n Perennium Blaster Rebuild Kit 260729\n\nPerennium Sniper Rebuild Kit\n+\nSuperior Perennium Blaster\n=\n<img src=rdb://244931>\n Superior Rebuilt Perennium Blaster 260706"), array(776,"Sword of Dusk - Sword of Dawn","\nIngredients \n\n Drops in Pandemonium, requires 30.000 faction to wear so neutrals can not use it since they are capped at 25.000. Both weapons can be upgraded with a Xan Weapon Upgrade Device 280786 \n\nOmni:\n Novictum Seed 246817\n<img src=rdb://246816>\nand\n Sunset Hilt 246814\n<img src=rdb://235341>\n\nor\n\nClan:\n Notum Seed 246818\n<img src=rdb://246815>\nand\n Sunrise Hilt 246813\n<img src=rdb://235342>\n\nRecipe \n\nNovictum Seed\n+\nSunset Hilt\n=\n<img src=rdb://246240>\n Sword of Dusk 246256\n\nor\n\nNotum Seed\n+\nSunrise Hilt\n=\n<img src=rdb://246241>\n Sword of Dawn 246244"), array(777,"Small Ingot Processing","\nIngredients \n\nSmall Silver Ingot, Small Gold Ingot and Small Platinum Ingot are used in variety of tradeskill processes. \n\n Precious Metal Reclaimer 150929\n<img src=rdb://149942>\n\n Personal Furnace 150930\n<img src=rdb://290713>\n\nA ring or bracer\n(ie: Flower Ring 136605)\n<img src=rdb://84046>\n\nRecipe \n\nNote: The initial process involves x3.2 in Mechanical Engineering Skill when dealing with Gold, x2.75 in Mechanical Engineering Skill when dealing with Silver both based on the QL of the material\n\nFlower Ring\n+\nPrecious Metal Reclaimer\n=\n<img src=rdb://289752>\n Small Silver Ingot 150912\n\nNote: Small Platinum Ingot 151363 can only be found from Mobs, Dyna & Mission bosses and as chestloot. Silver and Gold ingots can also be tradeskilled from:\n\n- Small Gold Ingot 151369 : Golden Sphere 136643 - Golden Ring 136599 - Marriage Ring 136607 - Bracer of Shielding - Projectile 84163 - Bracelet of Ka 136619 - Golden Bracer 136621 - Golden Nugget 136631 - Pink Ring 136615\n84163 84164 84165 84166 84167 84168 84169 84170 84171 84172 84173 84174 \n- Small Silver Ingot 150912 : Flower Ring 136605 - OT Ring 136609 - Silver Nugget 136635 - Ring of Luck - Defensive 84142 - Ring of Luck - Offensive 84143 - Ring of Power - Elements 84157 - Ring of Suffering 136617 - Ring of Zern 136601 - Snake Ring 136611 - Toe Ring 136657 - Engagement Ring 136603\n84175 84176 84177 84178 84179 84180 84181 84182 84183 84184 84185 84186 84147 84148 84149 84150 84153 84154 84155 84156\n- Known exceptions (will not melt to ingots): Augmented OT Ring 160424 - Excellent IQ Ring 84145 - Failed Ring of Flying 40828 - Fashionable Energy Ring 160739 - Silver Pearl 136653 - Ring of Knowledge 70255 - Gold 2 Sphere Pearl by Peters & Tool 25825 - Ring of Presence 160426 - Ring of the Nucleus Basalis 202718 - Ring of Thorns 136613 - Bracer of Growing Flesh 84187 - Bracer of Shrinking Flesh 84161 - Bracelet of Pacisfism 84188\n\n\nNote:Melting down metal will take x3 for Silver, x3.4 for Gold and x3.8 for Platinum in Mechanical Engineering Skill based on the QL of the Ingot.\n\nSmall Silver Ingot\n+\nPersonal Furnace\n=\n<img src=rdb://290705>\n Liquid Silver 150915"), array(780,"Chacolate Salty Balls","<yellow><end>\n<cyan>Ingredients<end>\n<yellow><end>\n<blue>\n<lime>-<end> 2/3 cup salted butter\n<lime>-<end> 1 1/2 cups sugar\n<lime>-<end> 1/4 cup brandy\n<lime>-<end> 4 cups semisweet chocolate chips\n<lime>-<end> 2 teaspoons vanilla extract\n<lime>-<end> 4 eggs\n<lime>-<end> 2 tablespoons cinnamon\n<lime>-<end> 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour\n<lime>-<end> 1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n<lime>-<end> 1/2 teaspoon table salt\n<lime>-<end> Coarse sea salt, to taste<end>\n<end>\n\n<yellow><end>\n<cyan>Recipe Directions<end>\n<yellow><end>\n\n<green>\nIn a saucepan, bring the butter, sugar and brandy to a boil, stirring constantly. Remove from the heat. Stir (with a wooden spoon) in 2 cups of chocolate chips until melted. Remember to give that spoon a lick! Cool mixture slightly. Stir in vanilla. In a large mixing bowl, beat the eggs. Gradually add the chocolate mixture and mix well. Combine the flour, baking soda and salt, then gradually add the dry ingredients to the chocolate mixture. Stir in any remaining chocolate chips. Spread into a greased baking pan. Bake at 325 degrees for 35-45 minutes or until a fork inserted in the center comes out clean. Careful not to burn your balls! Let cool just enough that it won't burn your hands. Meanwhile set up a small plate or cutting board with some of the sea salt on it. Scrape up the brownie mix, working around the edges. You don't want to use the hard edges for the balls. Begin shaping 1 inch balls out of the mix, give or take in size. Roll the balls in the salt. Do this very lightly (I suggest you do NOT try to emulate the picture), a little sea salt goes a very long way. If you do happen to oversalt, just brush the excess salt crystals off. Too much salt is bad, mmmkay? You're done, put 'em in your mouth and suck 'em! \n<end>"), array(781,"Windguaerd's Peruvian Ceviche","<yellow><end>\n<cyan>Ingredients<end>\n<yellow><end>\n<blue>\n<lime>-<end> 2 lbs tilapia fillets or 2 lbs other firm white fish fillets, cubed\n<lime>-<end> 8 -10 garlic cloves, chopped\n<lime>-<end> 1 teaspoon salt\n<lime>-<end> 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n<lime>-<end> 2 teaspoons fresh cilantro, chopped\n<lime>-<end> 8 -12 limes, freshly squeezed and strained to remove pulp, enough to cover fish\n<lime>-<end> 1 red onion, thinly sliced and rinsed\n<end>\n\n<yellow><end>\n<cyan>Optional:<end>\n<yellow><end>\n<blue>\n<lime>-<end> 1 habanero pepper, seeded and chopped (or real Peruvian Aji Amarillo, if you can find it)\n<end>\n\n<yellow><end>\n<cyan>Recipe Directions<end>\n<yellow><end>\n\n<green>\n1. Combine all ingredients except red onion and mix well.\n2. Place red onion on top and let it marinate in the refrigerator for at least 2-3 hours before serving.\n3. Before serving, mix well and serve with lettuce, corn, avocado or other cold salad vegetables on the side.\n4. It is important to use a juicer that presses the juice out of the limes, not one that will tear the membrane of the lime sections since this will make the lime juice bitter.\n<end>\n\n<yellow>Servings: 6<end>"), array(798,"Bastion","<img src=rdb://291379><img src=rdb://293723><img src=rdb://291371>\n\n<yellow>\n<cyan>Ingredients <green>\n<yellow>\n\n<green>- 3x <img src=rdb://292793> Inert Bacteriophage 292507\n- 1x <img src=rdb://292775> Virus Programming: Bacteriophage M73 292509\n- 1x <img src=rdb://292776> Virus Programming: Bacteriophage Phi X 3957 292508\n- 1x <img src=rdb://292774> Virus Programming: Bacteriophage F9 292510\n- 1x <img src=rdb://292764> Red Data Crystal 292514\n- 1x <img src=rdb://292780> Blue Data Crystal 292515\n- 1x <img src=rdb://292792> Green Data Crystal 292516\n- 3x <img src=rdb://292762> Pattern Conversion Device 292517\n- 3x <img src=rdb://292760> Nickel-Cobalt Ferrous Alloy 2925